1. Headers
markdown
# Heading 1
## Heading 2
### Heading 3
#### Heading 4
##### Heading 5
###### Heading 6
2. Emphasis (Bold & Italic)
markdown
*Italic text* or _Italic text_  
**Bold text** or __Bold text__  
***Bold & Italic*** or ___Bold & Italic___
3. Lists
Unordered List (Bullet Points):

markdown
- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Sub-item (indent with 2 spaces or a tab)
* Alternative bullet
Ordered List (Numbered):

markdown
1. First item
2. Second item
   1. Sub-item (indent with 3 spaces)
4. Links & Images
Link:

markdown
[Text](https://example.com)
Image:

markdown
![Alt Text](image.jpg "Optional Title")
5. Code & Syntax Highlighting
Inline Code:

markdown
`print("Hello, World!")`
Code Block (Indent with 4 spaces or use triple backticks):

markdown
```python
def hello():
    print("Hello, World!")
text
6. Blockquotes
markdown
> This is a blockquote.
> Multiple lines work too.
7. Horizontal Rule
markdown
---
or
***
or
___
8. Tables
markdown
| Header 1 | Header 2 |
|----------|----------|
| Cell 1   | Cell 2   |
| Cell 3   | Cell 4   |
9. Strikethrough
markdown
~~Strikethrough text~~
10. Escaping Characters
Use \ before special characters to display them literally:

markdown
\*Not italic\*
Extended Markdown (GFM - GitHub Flavored Markdown)
Task Lists:

markdown
- [x] Completed task
- [ ] Incomplete task
Emoji (in supported environments like GitHub):

markdown
:smile: :heart: :rocket:
Where to Use Markdown?
GitHub (README.md, comments, issues)

Reddit, Discord, Slack (some formatting)

Static site generators (Jekyll, Hugo)

Note-taking apps (Obsidian, Notion, Typora)



